(fifthQuint)Stereotactic Image-Guided Navigation During Breast Reconstruction in Patients With Breast Cancer.

 PRIMARY OBJECTIVES: I.

 To analyze the accuracy of preoperative CT angiography in determining the location of perforator vessels.

 Through the use of an intraoperative navigation system, we will objectively locate perforators during surgery and compare the results to the preoperative imaging assessment of the flap's vascular anatomy.

 II.

 To determine whether the preoperative CT angiogram allows the microsurgeon to correctly identify the perforators that are ultimately used as the pedicle for the flap.

 OUTLINE: Patients undergo deep inferior epigastric perforator (DIEP) flap breast reconstruction using the StealthStation navigation system.

 After completion of study treatment, patients are followed up at 1-2 weeks and 1 month, then every 3 months for 2 years.

